Source: nwu
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Yves Junqueira <yves@cetico.org>
Build-Depends: cdbs (>= 0.4.23-1.1), build-essential, debhelper (>= 4.1.0), python-dev
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: nwu-agent
Architecture: all
Depends: adduser, ${python:Depends}
Description: Network-wide updates for apt-able systems
 Nwu lets administrators manage APT of remote machines from one central point.
 It can do many apt tasks remotely, like update, upgrade and install. Also it
 provides relevant information about each node, like listing current installed
 packages, upgrade candidates and APT repositories and some basic system inf-
 ormation.
 .
 This package installs the nwu agent software, but you also need the nwu ser-
 ver somewhere in your network.

Package: nwu-server
Architecture: all
Depends: adduser, ${python:Depends}, m2crypto
Description: Network-wide updates for apt-able systems
 Nwu lets administrators manage APT of remote machines from one central point.
 It can do many apt tasks remotely, like update, upgrade and install. Also it
 provides relevant information about each node, like listing current installed
 packages, upgrade candidates and APT repositories and some basic system inf-
 ormation.
 .
 This package installs the nwu server software
